# SRT Chapter Splitter — Walkthrough

## Summary

Built a complete PyQt6 desktop application for splitting YouTube SRT subtitle files into chapters using AI. The app supports two script types (Top/List and Narrative), batch processing, automatic chapter verification, and multi-endpoint API failover.

## Project Structure

```
2.Script_Split_Chapter/
├── main.py                         # Entry point
├── requirements.txt                # PyQt6, requests
├── core/
│   ├── api_client.py               # Multi-endpoint API router + failover
│   ├── config_manager.py           # JSON config save/load per-tab
│   ├── srt_parser.py               # SRT file parser
│   ├── chapter_splitter.py         # AI chapter splitting + verification
│   └── process_controller.py       # ThreadPoolExecutor + start/pause/stop
├── ui/
│   ├── theme.py                    # Dark/Light QSS theme system
│   ├── icons/arrow_down.svg        # ComboBox/SpinBox arrows
│   ├── icons/arrow_up.svg
│   ├── searchable_combo.py         # Searchable QComboBox
│   ├── log_section.py              # Processing Log panel
│   ├── header_bar.py               # App title + Restart + Settings
│   ├── settings_dialog.py          # API endpoints + theme + dependencies
│   ├── projects_section.py         # Tree view with folder grouping
│   ├── chapter_tab.py              # Main tab: config + projects + actions
│   └── main_window.py              # Main window assembly
└── prompts/
    ├── system_toplist.txt           # Top/List script prompt
    ├── system_narrative.txt         # Narrative script prompt
    ├── system_verify.txt            # Verification prompt
    └── fallback_chapter.txt         # Fallback default prompt
```

## Key Features

| Feature | Implementation |
|---------|---------------|
| Dark/Light theme | [ui/theme.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/theme.py) — centralized QSS with [apply_theme()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/theme.py#392-398) |
| Multi-endpoint failover | [core/api_client.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/api_client.py) — auto-switch on 429/5xx |
| Batch processing | [core/process_controller.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/process_controller.py) — ThreadPoolExecutor |
| Start/Pause/Stop | State machine with `threading.Event` |
| Config persistence | Per-tab JSON files (`chapter_config.json`) |
| API logging | Optional JSONL logging to `logs/api_history.jsonl` |
| Auto-save | Results saved per-item immediately on completion |
| Chapter verification | AI verification step before final output |
| External prompts | [.txt](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/requirements.txt) files in `prompts/` — editable without code changes |
| File management | Scan folder, add files, dedup, tree view grouping |
| Output | Per-chapter [.txt](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/requirements.txt), merged file, summary file |

## Verification

- **Import check**: `python -c "from ui.main_window import MainWindow; ..."` — **passed**
- **App launch**: `python main.py` — **running without errors**
